oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Lespedeza in soil bank
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Young, Hiram J., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: One-year-old stand of sericea lespedeza seeded on Class II Dickson soil. Land is in Soil Bank Program. Portion has been clipped. 7 mi. S. Woodbury on Red Hill Road.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
